history.content: it looks like all 3 CS classes expanded last Fall to accommodate waitlists, so you should put yourself on the waitlist when registering.  Probably will get into all 3, though no guarantees.

Hi Guys,

I'm a visiting student and I'm currently classified as an undeclared major for registration purposes. I am planning to take CS 170, CS 188, CS 161 and History 10. Of these classes, which do you guys reckon I would be able to get into by the end of Phase 2. I am registering on Friday and will be placed on the waitlist I believe.

For example, I'd like to take CS 188 but CS 188 seems to have open seats of 192, and 300+ people on the waitlist right now. Would it be worth still enrolling or should I switch to Math 54 which has open unreserved seats?

Thanks
history.subject: Classes I will be able to get into by the end of phase 2
